-- per-type Hashable hasher: hashString is FNV-1a over the String cell's raw UTF-8
-- bytes, masked to [0, 2^30).  This is the CONTENT-hashing the old structural
-- __hashRaw gave but the type-erased native runtime could not — equal Strings must
-- hash equal across backends.  Byte-identical to runtime/medaka_rt.c mdk_hash_string.
main = hashString "hello"
